# Analysis

## Time Complexity Comparison

### Linear Search
- **Best Case:** O(1)
- **Average Case:** O(n)
- **Worst Case:** O(n)

### Binary Search
- **Best Case:** O(1)
- **Average Case:** O(log n)
- **Worst Case:** O(log n)

## Comparison

- Linear Search checks each product one by one until the target is found.
- Binary Search repeatedly divides the sorted array into halves.
- Binary Search requires the array to be sorted before searching.
- Binary Search performs fewer comparisons than Linear Search for large datasets.

## Suitable Algorithm for the Platform

- Binary Search is more suitable for an e-commerce platform.
- It provides faster search performance for large product catalogs.
- It improves the user experience by reducing search time.
- It is highly efficient when products are stored in sorted order.
- Linear Search is suitable only for small or unsorted datasets.
